<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>

    <metal:portlets fill-slot="portlets">
      <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-latestspecs" />
    </metal:portlets>

<metal:heading fill-slot="pageheading">
  <h1>Implementation roadmap</h1>
</metal:heading>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <p>
    Launchpad recommends the following sequence of feature implementations.
  </p>

  <p class="informational message" tal:condition="not: view/spec_plan">
    No specifications for
    <span tal:replace="context/displayname">Ubuntu Hoary</span>
    exist that can be scheduled.
  </p>

  <tal:block condition="view/spec_plan">
    <table>
      <tr tal:repeat="spec view/spec_plan"
          tal:replace="structure spec/@@+listing-simple" />
    </table>
  </tal:block>

</div>

    <p metal:fill-slot="help">
      Blueprints should be implemented in the order given.
      This will ensure that the most important blueprints are implemented
      first, and that blueprint dependencies are respected.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
